This paper is about improving distant supervised relation extraction using a novel dynamic neural network. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to handle long-tail classes, which is a common problem in machine learning and can be addressed using techniques from the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of dynamic parameters, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and can be found in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves text classification and information retrieval, which are topics covered in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
